condition.narrative: Section I.A.1 of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement: Government of Malawi (GoM) shall establish by not later than three (3)months after effectiveness, and thereafter maintain throughout the period of Project implementation, a Project steering committee,headed by the Secretary of Education (MoE) and co-chaired by Secretary of Labor (MoL), with composition terms of reference, andfunctions, responsibilities and adequate resources, satisfactory to the Association, as further elaborated in the ProjectImplementation Manual (PIM).

Section I.A.3(a) of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement: GoM shall establish, by no later than one (1) month after effectiveness,and thereafter maintain throughout the period of Project implementation, a technical committee headed by the Director of HigherEducation (MoE) co-chaired by the Director of Technical and and Vocational Training (MoL), with composition/membership satisfactoryto the Association, with terms of reference, functions, responsibilities and adequate resources, satisfactory to the Association,as further elaborated in the PIM.

Section I.A.4 of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement: GoM shall, by not later than nine (9) months after effectiveness, procureand engage, and thereafter maintain throughout the implementation period of the IDP Grants, the services of an independentverification consulting firm, with qualification and experience, and under terms of reference, satisfactory to the Association, asset forth in the PIM, for purposes of carrying out the independent verification of the milestones and/or results achieved in theimplementation of the said IDP Grants.

Section I.B.1 & 2 of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement: GoM shall: (a) prepare and formally adopt (by effectiveness), a Projectimplementation manual, in a manner and substance acceptable to the Association; and (b) ensure and cause the PIE, PHEIs andTechnical Institutions to ensure, that the Project is carried out in accordance with the PIM.

Section I.C.1 of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement: GoM shall make part of the proceeds of the Financing allocated from time totime to Categories (3) and (5) of the table set forth in Section III.1 of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement available to theTEVETA pursuant to written agreements between GoM and TEVETA the Recipient and the PIE (the “Subsidiary Agreement”), under termsand conditions approved by the Association.

Section I.D.1 & 2 of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement: For purposes of Sub-Components 1.1 and 2.1 of the Project, GoM shall:(a) cause each public higher education institution (“PHEI”) or national technical college (“NTC”) participating in the Project toprepare its respective IDPs for financing under an IDP Grant in accordance with the procedures and requirements set forth in thePIM; (b) submit to the Association such IDP, together with its detailed results framework, proposed disbursement benchmarks,envisioned expenditures and costing, and overall funding request, for review and no-objection prior to its final approval by theProject Steering Committee and the award of the respective IDP Grant; and (c) upon approval of an IDP and the respective IDP Grant,enter into a written agreement with the respective PHEI or NTC, as the case may be (the “Performance Agreement”), to make part ofthe proceeds of the Financing (i.e. the IDP Grant) available to such PHEI or NTC, as the case may be, on terms conditions approvedby the Association as further elaborated in the PIM.

Section I.E.1&2 of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement: For purposes of carrying out the activities under Component 2.2 of theProject, GoM shall: (a) cause TEVETA to: (i) establish, by not later than three (3) month after the Effective Date, and thereaftermaintain throughout the period of implementation of its Respective Sub-Component(s), a selection committee of experts (the“Competitive Grant Committee”), membership and terms of reference, satisfactory to the Association, as set forth in the CompetitiveFund Guidelines, to be responsible for, inter alia: (A) coordinating the call for IDP proposals and carrying out the screening andselection thereof, as per item (iii) below; and (B) providing technical advice to TEVETA, the PIU and the PSC, as needed, inrespect to Sub-Component 2.2 of the Project; (ii) thereafter, publicly call CTCs, PTCs and CSDCs to submit their respective IDPproposals together with their funding requests, agreed cooperation arrangements with private sector and, as required, theircounterpart funding commitments, in accordance with the procedures and requirements set forth in the Competitive Fund Guidelines;(iii) have the Competitive Grant Committee: (A) screen the above referred IDP proposals and the respective applicant as per theprotocols, eligibility criteria and prioritization principles set forth in the Competitive Fund Guidelines; (B) submit to theAssociation the tentative list of competitively selected IDP proposal and awardees, as well as the proposed subgrant amounts, forthe Association’s review and no-objection; and, thereafter (C) propose for approval by the Project Steering Committee the finallist of competitively selected IDP proposals and awardees, and their respective subgrant amounts (each a “Competitive Grant”),taking into consideration the Association’s comments and no-objections, for the financing under the Project; and (b) upon theProject Steering Committee’s approving the award of a Competitive Grant by the Competitive Grant Committee pursuant to subparagraph (a) above, cause TEVETA to enter into a written agreement (the “Competitive Grant Agreement”) with such selectedTechnical Institution -other than the NTCs- to make part of the proceeds of the Financing (i.e. the approved Competitive Grant)available to such Technical Institution, on terms and conditions agreed by the Association, as further elaborated in theCompetitive Fund Guidelines.

Section I.G.1 of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement: GoM shall: (a) by no later than January 31 of each year during theimplementation of the Project, prepare and furnish to the Association an annual work plan and budget containing all activitiesproposed to be included in the Project during the following Financial Year, and the proposed financing plan for the expendituresrequired thereunder, indicating the amounts and source of financing (“Annual Work Plan and Budget”), all in accordance with thePIM; and (b) afford the Association a reasonable opportunity to exchange views with the Recipient on each such Annual Work Plan andBudget and, thereafter, ensure that the Project is implemented with due diligence during said following Financial Year inaccordance with said Annual Work Plan and Budget as shall have been approved by the Project Steering Committee taking intoconsideration the comments/suggestions provided by the Association. Notwithstanding, the provision above the first Annual WorkPlan and Budget will be prepared and submitted by not later than forty-five (45) days after the Effective Date.

Sections I.H1&2 of the Schedule to the Financing Agreements: GoM shall, and shall case the PHEIs, Technical Institutions andTEVETA, to ensure that the Project is: (i) carried out in accordance with the Environmental and Social Standards in a manneracceptable to the Association; (ii) implemented in accordance with the ESCP in a manner acceptable to the Association, includingactions and measure specified therein to be implemented with due diligence and efficiency, the provision of sufficient fundstherefor, and the maintenance of policies, procedures and retention of qualified staff in adequate numbers, as specified in theESCP.
